Former New York Giants Toomer, Oben to Cover High School Football for MSG

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-08-30T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/former-new-york-giants-toomer-oben-to-cover-high-school-football-for-msg.html
Former  New York  Giants Amani Toomer
and Roman Oben will be color analysts for Friday night football
games on MSG Varsity, a Cablevision Systems Corp. network
dedicated to high school sports in the New York area.  Toomer, who holds the Giants’ record for postseason
receptions, will provide color commentary for  MSG Varsity ’s
“Friday Night Football” games throughout New York,  New Jersey 
and Connecticut. Oben will work as an analyst for games in
Westchester, New York, the network said in a press release.  MSG Varsity, which is available exclusively to
Cablevision’s iO TV subscribers in the tri-state area, begins
its coverage of high school football on Sept. 9.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net  